@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@
+# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260323-125539-3bf4
+## Findings
+1. [P2] Fix 1 — Dish cards have no card-level detail handler. `MenuView.jsx:84-87` and `MenuView.jsx:193-196` render the list and tile `<Card>` wrappers without any `onClick`, so tapping the card body cannot open a dish detail surface. The only dish-selection callback in `MenuView.jsx` is the review widget click at `MenuView.jsx:140-143` and `MenuView.jsx:253-256`, which does not cover “tap anywhere on card”. FIX: pass a dedicated `onDishClick(dish)` prop from `x.jsx`, attach it to both card wrappers, and add `stopPropagation()` to the list-mode `+/-` controls before enabling the parent click so stepper taps stay isolated.
+2. [P2] Fix 1 — The selected-dish flow is still wired to a reviews-only modal, not a full dish detail view. `x.jsx:1314` stores only `selectedDishId`, `x.jsx:1768-1777` fetches only feedback records, `x.jsx:3276` passes only `onOpenReviews` into `MenuView`, and `x.jsx:3612-3618` opens `DishReviewsModal` with only `dishTitle`, `reviews`, and `loading`. That contract cannot render the image, description, price, and “Add to cart” action required by PM-102 even after card taps are wired. FIX: change the page-level selection flow from “open reviews” to “open dish detail”, and pass selected dish data plus `addToCart` into the overlay; if reviews remain part of the same surface, load them inside that detail view.
+3. [P2] Fix 2 — Add-to-cart currently drives two different toast renderers for the same action. `x.jsx:2316-2324` already shows a `sonner` success toast when an item is added, but `MenuView.jsx:54-67` and `MenuView.jsx:373-375` still keep a second fixed in-page toast for the same event. The page therefore has a legacy custom toast path alongside the shared toast API, which is the most likely source of the malformed “thin line” Android notification. FIX: keep a single toast system, remove the legacy `toastVisible`/fixed toast block from `MenuView.jsx`, and style the shared `sonner` toast path for a 375px mobile viewport.
+4. [P2] Fix 3 — Tile-mode discount pricing still allows uncontrolled wrapping. In `MenuView.jsx:236-245`, the discounted price row is a plain inline flex row with no `flex-nowrap`, no `whitespace-nowrap`, and no tile-specific font reduction. On a narrow two-column mobile tile, the discounted amount and the `₸` symbol can wrap into 3+ lines. FIX: constrain the tile price block to one-line or explicit two-line behavior by using `whitespace-nowrap` on each price chunk and either `flex-nowrap` or a deliberate `flex-col items-start` layout with smaller text and tighter leading.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 4 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 4 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 specifies a full dish-detail view, but the target files only expose a reviews-modal flow and do not identify the intended detail component contract; Fix 4 points to `x.jsx` or `CartView.jsx`, while the scope lock and speed rules restrict the review to `MenuView.jsx`, `x.jsx`, `README.md`, and `BUGS.md`.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): whether a shared `sonner` `<Toaster>` is mounted outside this page, and whether the intended PM-102 fix should extend `DishReviewsModal` or replace it with a different detail sheet/dialog.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): whether Fix 4 should be treated as reviewable when the chevron/separator markup is not present in the two target files and the task explicitly forbids reading the likely owning file.
